    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-09T12:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-09T12:24:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760i.61/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-09T19:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1920—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 10—3:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>100. Esthonia Minister of Foreign Affairs expects to receive within next few days
                    demand from Moscow that Esthonia immediately join federated Soviet Russia.
                    Esthonia will probably refuse and in that event armed conflict will doubtless
                    follow. Many arrests Bolshevik sympathizers Reval yesterday.</p>
                <p>British are preparing plans for evacuation if necessary of their subjects from
                    Baltic Provinces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
